; call-position-shadow-band.fk — witness that locals ECLIPSE globals in call
; position (the cell-capture class of
; receipts/2026-07-17-jacobian-lens-and-the-cell-shadowing-heal.md, healed in
; receipts/2026-07-17-locals-eclipse-globals-in-call-position.md).
;
; Verdict 7 when every claim lands:
;   1  a defn parameter whose name equals a global defn answers the call —
;      (defn offer (cell args) (cell args)) invokes the PARAMETER's fn-value,
;      not the global (defn cell ...) constructor
;   2  the global still answers when no local stands between (the eclipse is
;      positional, not a deletion)
;   4  a let-bound fn-value eclipses the same global in call position too
;
; Pre-heal runtimes (defn table consulted before the local frame) answer 2:
; bits 1 and 4 capture to the global and return 111 where 6 is true.
;
; Run:
;   ./fkwu --src form/form-stdlib/tests/call-position-shadow-band.fk

(do
    (defn cell (x) 111)
    (defn bump (n) (add n 1))
    (defn offer (cell args) (cell args))
    (defn via-let (f n) (do (let cell f) (cell n)))
    (defn cpsb-bit (ok bit) (if ok bit 0))
    (add (cpsb-bit (eq (offer bump 5) 6) 1)
    (add (cpsb-bit (eq (cell 1) 111) 2)
         (cpsb-bit (eq (via-let bump 5) 6) 4))))
